title: George Osborne: 'We'll govern for the many'
text:
Media playback is unsupported on your device
George Osborne: 'We'll govern for the many' 5 October 2015 Last updated at 13:16 BST
George Osborne has told Conservative Party members to "extend a hand" to voters who felt unable to trust the party at the last election.
Speaking at the party's conference in Manchester, the chancellor said that the Tories must not rest on their laurels after winning a mandate to stay in government.
And he promised to stand up for working people.
